<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="162" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,729,935]" pageId="1" pageNumber="162">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rubsaamen" authorityYear="1892" box="[151,300,729,755]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Rhopalomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="162" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,300,729,755]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="162">Rhopalomyia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a worldwide genus of the tribe 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Felt" authorityYear="1908" box="[705,860,729,755]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="162" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Oligotrophini">Oligotrophini</taxonomicName>
, with 267 valid known species, associated almost exclusively with galls on 
<taxonomicName authority="(Gagne &amp; Jaschhof 2017)" authorityName="Gagne &amp; Jaschhof" authorityYear="2017" baseAuthorityName="Gagne &amp; Jaschhof" baseAuthorityYear="2017" box="[447,880,765,791]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="1" pageNumber="162" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">
Asteraceae (
<bibRefCitation author="Gagne, R. J. &amp; Jaschhof, M." box="[587,872,765,791]" pageId="1" pageNumber="162" refId="ref4539" refString="Gagne, R. J. &amp; Jaschhof, M. (2017) A catalog of the Cecidomyiidae (Diptera) of the World. 4 th Edition. Digital Version. Systematic Entomology Laboratory, Agricultural Research Service, U. S. Department of Agriculture U. S. National Museum, Washington, D. C., 762 pp. Available from: https: // www. ars. usda. gov / ARSUserFiles / 80420580 / Gagne _ 2017 _ World _ Cat _ 4 th _ ed. pdf (accessed 21 June 2018)" type="book" year="2017">Gagné &amp; Jaschhof 2017</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. Typically, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rubsaamen" authorityYear="1892" box="[1013,1162,765,791]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Rhopalomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="162" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1013,1162,765,791]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="162">Rhopalomyia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species have a reduced number of palpal segments, one or two, but some species have three to four segments; vein C is not interrupted immediately posterior to its juncture with R5; tarsal claws may or not may have basal tooth; in the female the eighth abdominal tergite is undivided longitudinally and the cerci are fused; males with completely setulose gonostyle. Larva with or without spatula.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
